They discovered that the functioning of the Sun is based on the same basic principles as other stars: the activity of all the stars in the solar system is determined by nothing other than their luminosity and rotation.
The luminosity is used together with the rotation to define the Rossby number of a star, which is linked to the plasma flow.
The lower the number of Rossby, the less the activity of the star compared to the magnetic inversions.
